.SH NOTES
.sp
.LP
Each \fBUTF-16\fR or \fBUTF-32\fR character maps to an \fBUTF-8\fR character that might need one to maximum of four bytes.
.sp
.LP
One \fBUTF-32\fR or \fBUTF-8\fR character can yield two 16-bit unsigned integers as a \fBUTF-16\fR character, which is a surrogate pair if the Unicode scalar value is bigger than \fBU+FFFF\fR.
.sp
.LP
Ill-formed \fBUTF-16\fR surrogate pairs are seen as illegal characters during the conversion.
